# HyBBX project rules

Read [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md) and [docs/DEVELOPMENT.md](../../docs/DEVELOPMENT.md).

## Product

Plugin-only session daemon; Main + Secondary HBX topology ([TOPOLOGY.md](../../docs/TOPOLOGY.md)). **v1.5.0** — [RELEASE-1.5.0.md](../../docs/RELEASE-1.5.0.md). Technical docs in `docs/`; root README is short overview.

## Code

- C99, `hybbx_` prefix, `hybbx_result_t` errors
- Core = sessions + HBX/TCP only — no wire-protocol parsing in `src/core/`
- Plugins in `plugins/`; booleans via `hybbx_parse_bool()`
- Minimal scope; [limits.h](../../include/hybbx/limits.h)

## Docs

- Feature changes → FEATURES.md. Config → MANUAL.md + `share/hybbx.ini.example` (keep INI comments short).
- Commands → [COMMANDS.md](../../docs/COMMANDS.md) + [share/commands.yaml](../../share/commands.yaml); help format in [AGENTS.md](../../AGENTS.md).
- **Current version only** — no prior-version references in docs, `text/`, or user-facing comments.
- **As-is software** — compact prose; no upgrade/migration/history sections.
- **Linux-based documentation** — `docs/`, `text/`, README, share examples. `HTTPD_DOCROOT`, `systemctl`, `ss`. No other OS names (BSD, macOS, Windows, …) or distro-specific package paths.
- On version bump: replace release docs; delete superseded `docs/RELEASE-*.md`.

## Git

Public: `user.name=ngteq`, empty email; no agent `Co-authored-by`. No commit/push unless user asks.
